subject:  58)! where can i get patch to x11r5?

	the releas of new public patch by the mit x consortium is announc
in the comp.window.x.announc newsgroup.

	patch themselv ar avail via ftp from export and from other
site from which x11 is avail. thei ar now also distribut through the 
newsgroup comp.sourc.x. some sourc re-seller mai be includ patch in 
their sourc distribut of x11.

	peopl without ftp access can us the xstuff mail server. it now ha 
23 patch for x11r5 [3/93].  send to xstuff@expo.lc.mit.edu the subject line
		send fix #
where # is the name of the patch and is usual just the number of the patch.

	here ar a few complic:
	1) fix 5 is in four part; you need to request "5a", "5b", "5c" and 
"5d" separ
	2) the file sungx.uu, which wa part of an earlier patch, wa 
re-releas with patch 7 [note: the file doesn't work with solari]
	3) fix 8 is in two part: "8a" and "8b"
	4) fix 13 is in three part: "13a", "13b", and "13c"
	5) fix 16 is in two part: "16a" and "16b"
	6) fix 18 replac the r5fix-test1 for the x test suit, which 
previous wa option
	7) fix 19 also need pexlib.tar.z, which you can obtain from xstuff
by ask for "pexlib.uu.[1234]".
	8) fix 22 is in 9 part, "22a" through "22i"

